        "Create a half-equation balancing comparison table for MnO₄⁻, Cr₂O₇²⁻, and IO₃⁻ reduction in acid. Columns: (1) species and product; (2) O atoms to balance; (3) H₂O molecules added; (4) H⁺ added; (5) electrons gained; (6) final half-equation. Completing this table for three different species, side by side, forces the pattern recognition that the method is identical regardless of the species.",
        "Create a redox titration comparison table. Columns: (1) oxidant; (2) reductant; (3) acid used; (4) colour change at endpoint; (5) self-indicating?; (6) indicator if not self-indicating; (7) molar ratio; (8) when indicator is added. Rows: KMnO₄/Fe²⁺; K₂Cr₂O₇/Fe²⁺; I₂/S₂O₃²⁻. Fill all 24 cells. Cover column 7 and reconstruct molar ratios from the balanced equations — this is the most frequently lost mark in titration calculations.",
